               <head>Revenues and description of Bengal</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary />
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh94006886 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064915" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4499-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Revenue records, in Persian with raqam annotation, for the province of the  <name key="http://lccn.loc.gov/n81059698" type="place">Bengal</name> khāliṣah-'i sharīfah, including detailed lists of naz̲rānah, ḥāṣilnivīsī, rasmnivīsī, zar-i chawth, jāgīr, and khāliṣah properties and procedures, over the banglah years 1169, 1171, 1172, 1180 
                        </p>
                        <p>Special mention is made in one section of properties assigned to the Bakhshī al-mamālik </p>
                        <p>Note in English at beginning, <q>From Kissen Chund the Naib Canongoi of Bengal, June 1788</q>
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated oval seals of James Grant at beginning and end: Jams Grānt ṣadr-i sarishtah'dār (sic) va mulāḥiẓ-i kull-i dafātir az ṭaraf-i dīvān-i ṣūbah'jāt-i Bangālah va Bihār va gairah, madār al-mahām sipah sālār-i Angrīz-i Kampanī, sanah 1193 Bangalah </p>
                        <p>Green leather binding </p>
                        <p>Not dated and lacking colophon </p>
                        <p>Partially foliated in Persian; estimated 131 folios (24 + 80 + 4 + 23) approximately </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
